 to have a big brass lamp that stood up about this high with a pink shade on it, oil lamp. Yes. That was on Sundays. Yes, I forgot, he used to read out of one of the girls books or Little Folk or Chatterbox I think we used to have every year, Uncle Lou us
ed to send every year you know. One was called Little Folks and the other was Chatterbox. The girls used to have one each. He used to read us a serial sort of story out of that. Well made it a serial by reading a section each Sunday evening.
